1
00:00:14,916 --> 00:00:16,166
[KAZUKI]
That's right.

2
00:00:16,250 --> 00:00:18,875
I dress as Sara Azuma
and take selfies.

3
00:00:18,958 --> 00:00:21,416
I know, I'm messed up.
[sniffles]

4
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:23,625
[KEPPI]
Now now, it's been a long day.

5
00:00:23,708 --> 00:00:25,000
Take it easy.

6
00:00:25,083 --> 00:00:27,791
How about a little gift
in return for your aid?

7
00:00:27,875 --> 00:00:28,750
[grunts]

8
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:31,000
[shimmering]

9
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:36,166
♪

10
00:00:36,250 --> 00:00:37,958
[shimmering]

11
00:00:38,041 --> 00:00:41,291
[steam hissing]

12
00:00:41,375 --> 00:00:43,375
[BOTH gasping]

13
00:00:47,375 --> 00:00:49,333
[gasps]

14
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:52,291
This shall grant you
any wish you desire.

15
00:00:52,375 --> 00:00:55,083
It is known as the Dish of Hope.

16
00:00:55,166 --> 00:00:57,208
Now, heed my words carefully.

17
00:00:57,291 --> 00:00:58,708
As heir to the throne

18
00:00:58,791 --> 00:01:00,416
-of the Kappa Kingdom, I...
-[KAZUKI] Anything?

19
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:03,500
Even, like, a year's
supply of cucumber rolls?

20
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:09,125
-[thudding]
-[ALL yelling]

21
00:01:09,208 --> 00:01:10,583
-[thudding]
-[KAZUKI grunts]

22
00:01:10,666 --> 00:01:12,000
Your wish is granted.

23
00:01:12,083 --> 00:01:14,666
-[shattering]
-[gasps]

24
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:18,083
-That's not fair. One more try!
-[TOI] He wasn't lying.

25
00:01:18,166 --> 00:01:21,208
I need you to transform
in order to remove shirikodama

26
00:01:21,291 --> 00:01:23,250
from the kappa zombies
as you did today.

27
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:24,958
A small price to pay,

28
00:01:25,041 --> 00:01:28,250
considering that you'll have
your wishes granted.

29
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:30,291
[birds chirping]

30
00:01:32,041 --> 00:01:34,208
[KAZUKI]
Any wish at all?

31
00:01:34,291 --> 00:01:36,750
-[HARUKA] Hey, Kazu.
-[KAZUKI] Hmm?

32
00:01:36,833 --> 00:01:39,791
Today, let's bring Nyantaro
some Fish Buffet,

33
00:01:39,875 --> 00:01:42,000
since I know
that's his favorite!

34
00:01:42,083 --> 00:01:44,500
[KAZUKI] This is Haruka.
My little brother.

35
00:01:44,583 --> 00:01:47,500
[HARUKA]
Hi, Sara! Good morning!

36
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:51,000
I wanted to know,
do you like cats?

37
00:01:51,083 --> 00:01:53,250
And... send.

38
00:01:53,333 --> 00:01:57,625
[KAZUKI] "Harukappa"
is Haruka's online handle.

39
00:01:57,708 --> 00:01:59,875
[HARUKA]
Hi, Sara! Good morning!

40
00:01:59,958 --> 00:02:02,291
I wanted to know,
do you like cats?

41
00:02:02,375 --> 00:02:06,875
[KAZUKI] Good morning!
Yeah! I'm crazy for kitty cats!

42
00:02:06,958 --> 00:02:08,791
[sighs]

43
00:02:08,875 --> 00:02:11,916
[KAZUKI] This is how I keep
my connection with Haruka.

44
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,875
By pretending to be Sara Azuma.

45
00:02:14,958 --> 00:02:17,416
My brother is the reason...

46
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:19,958
why I have to get
a Dish of Hope.

47
00:03:51,416 --> 00:03:53,166
Sara Azuma here!

48
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:57,750
With my lucky selfies, you'll
be happy every single day!

49
00:03:57,833 --> 00:04:01,416
Get the dish! Harukappa, here!

50
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:04,916
Haruka, stop doing those silly
poses and eat your breakfast.

51
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,375
[HARUKA]
Yes ma'am.

52
00:04:06,458 --> 00:04:08,166
So tell me, "Harukappa,"

53
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:10,333
do your friends at school
call you that, too?

54
00:04:10,416 --> 00:04:15,083
[laughs] I don't know.
[gasps] Kazu!

55
00:04:15,166 --> 00:04:18,333
[KAZUKI'S MOM] Morning, Kazu!
Breakfast is ready.

56
00:04:18,416 --> 00:04:21,041
Thanks, but I'll pass.

57
00:04:21,125 --> 00:04:23,916
-Okay. Be safe out there.
-Wait for me!

58
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:27,125
-I wanna go!
-[KAZUKI'S DAD] All right, then.

59
00:04:29,125 --> 00:04:30,666
[HARUKA]
You know, I think Nyantaro

60
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:32,250
might be getting fatter.

61
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:35,041
He wasn't all round like that
when we first met him.

62
00:04:35,125 --> 00:04:38,125
-He looks the same.
-Huh. You think so?

63
00:04:38,208 --> 00:04:39,916
[laughs]

64
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,291
But that was so cool, you know,

65
00:04:42,375 --> 00:04:44,208
what you did. Remember?

66
00:04:44,291 --> 00:04:45,875
I said I wanted
a kitty for a pet,

67
00:04:45,958 --> 00:04:50,083
and you made it happen,
just like magic!

68
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:54,916
Okay! Let's look at our
lucky item for today!

69
00:04:57,041 --> 00:05:00,458
[SARA]
Meow! It's kitty cats!

70
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:03,458
Kitties make me
as happy as can be!

71
00:05:03,541 --> 00:05:06,583
That's good.
The real one likes cats, too.

72
00:05:06,666 --> 00:05:09,875
It's Sara! I didn't know
you were a Sara fan too!

73
00:05:09,958 --> 00:05:11,500
I'm not, not at all.

74
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:13,666
Well, I think
she's just the best!

75
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:16,666
Oh, hey! I'm gonna tell you
my biggest, coolest secret

76
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:18,416
that nobody else knows!

77
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:20,541
-Uh, it's fine.
-Guess what?

78
00:05:20,625 --> 00:05:22,583
Me and Sara
are actually friends!

79
00:05:22,666 --> 00:05:26,000
She sends me her lucky selfies
every day. Look!

80
00:05:26,083 --> 00:05:27,958
You sure someone isn't
fooling you?

81
00:05:28,041 --> 00:05:30,958
Don't be mean.
It's the real Sara, okay?

82
00:05:31,041 --> 00:05:33,041
You see? Right here!

83
00:05:33,125 --> 00:05:34,791
[KAZUKI]
That's me.

84
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:37,125
-[HARUKA] And here!
-[KAZUKI] Me.

85
00:05:37,208 --> 00:05:38,833
[HARUKA]
And here!

86
00:05:38,916 --> 00:05:40,166
[KAZUKI]
Also me.

87
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:42,666
[laughs]
I told you!

88
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:44,208
-[snaps fingers]
-Yes!

89
00:05:46,208 --> 00:05:49,750
-[harsh spraying]
-[groaning]

90
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:51,791
-[yells]
-[splashing]

91
00:05:51,875 --> 00:05:53,500
[gasps]

92
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:55,750
[CHIKAI] Ready to tell us where
you found out about this route?

93
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,916
Stop it! I don't know!

94
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,416
[CHIKAI] Listen, buddy,
we don't want want to be here

95
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:01,916
any more than you do.

96
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,666
Just fess up already,
so we can all go home.

97
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:06,791
[MAN grunting]

98
00:06:06,875 --> 00:06:08,375
[gasps]

99
00:06:09,958 --> 00:06:12,375
Well, you better make it quick.

100
00:06:14,125 --> 00:06:16,375
[CHIKAI]
Can you pull it together?

101
00:06:16,458 --> 00:06:19,333
I can't keep bailing you out
like this when you screw up.

102
00:06:19,416 --> 00:06:21,541
[TOI]
It won't happen again.

103
00:06:21,625 --> 00:06:23,541
So take me with you, okay?

104
00:06:23,625 --> 00:06:25,875
You'll only get in the way.

105
00:06:25,958 --> 00:06:29,708
We'll see after our next gig.
We might make a lot of cash.

106
00:06:29,791 --> 00:06:33,083
Of course, we're dead if anyone
catches wind of our plan first.

107
00:06:33,166 --> 00:06:34,375
You understand.

108
00:06:34,458 --> 00:06:36,958
If you want money,
then I can get plenty!

109
00:06:37,041 --> 00:06:38,833
Don't let me stop you!

110
00:06:38,916 --> 00:06:41,625
'Cause next time, you might be
the one bailing me out.

111
00:06:43,083 --> 00:06:45,833
[CHIKAI] Speaking of bailing,
I'd better go.

112
00:06:45,916 --> 00:06:48,875
Don't get in
over your head, Toi.

113
00:06:48,958 --> 00:06:50,416
You, too.

114
00:06:52,875 --> 00:06:54,875
[KAZUKI]
I'll do anything...

115
00:06:54,958 --> 00:06:57,833
to get a Dish of Hope
for my brother.

116
00:06:57,916 --> 00:06:59,458
[SARA]
Now, our next dish.

117
00:06:59,541 --> 00:07:01,750
A man's body was found
in the Sumida River,

118
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,333
and not the living kind.

119
00:07:03,416 --> 00:07:05,166
Uh-oh!

120
00:07:06,916 --> 00:07:09,625
Holy crap!

121
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:12,041
This is not my box.

122
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:13,583
Does this thing belong to Kuji?

123
00:07:13,666 --> 00:07:15,666
-[door slams]
-[yells]

124
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:17,083
Whoa! Jeez!

125
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:19,416
-Don't startle me!
-Stop yelling!

126
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:20,916
What is that?

127
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,875
I, uh, grabbed this by accident.
It's Kuji's package.

128
00:07:23,958 --> 00:07:26,416
Yeah? So did you two
make friends already?

129
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,916
[ENTA]
You gotta be kidding!

130
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,291
He's bad news!
I'm telling you!

131
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:33,458
♪

132
00:07:39,458 --> 00:07:42,708
[cell phone buzzes]

133
00:07:43,958 --> 00:07:47,375
-[TOI] Hey. Yeah, no prob.
-[NYANTARO growling]

134
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:49,666
[TOI] I got some
high-quality stuff this time.

135
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,250
Where?

136
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:53,208
-You got it.
-[growls]

137
00:07:53,291 --> 00:07:54,750
[thuds loudly]

138
00:07:56,666 --> 00:07:58,666
[growls]

139
00:08:00,041 --> 00:08:01,625
-[growls angrily]
-[TOI gasps]

140
00:08:01,708 --> 00:08:03,625
Hey! Stop!

141
00:08:03,708 --> 00:08:05,625
Come back!

142
00:08:05,708 --> 00:08:07,583
[KAZUKI]
This is a real pain.

143
00:08:07,666 --> 00:08:09,541
The one time I need cats
to be here,

144
00:08:09,625 --> 00:08:11,708
-I can't find any at all!
-[NYANTARO chattering]

145
00:08:12,791 --> 00:08:14,708
-[thudding]
-[KAZUKI yells, groans]

146
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:17,500
Nyantaro?

147
00:08:17,583 --> 00:08:21,000
Not quite what I wanted,
but you'll have to do.

148
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:23,000
[KAZUKI]
Where did you get that?

149
00:08:23,083 --> 00:08:25,166
-[TOI] You can't hide!
-[NYANTARO growls]

150
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:27,416
-[KAZUKI] Kuji?
-You little furry fat ass.

151
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,583
You give that back.

152
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:33,000
-[energy shimmering]
-[NYANTARO growls]

153
00:08:33,083 --> 00:08:34,958
[TOI]
I'm going to end you.

154
00:08:35,041 --> 00:08:37,041
-Cut it out!
-You first!

155
00:08:37,125 --> 00:08:38,750
[KAZUKI]
Haruka loves Nyantaro!

156
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:41,833
You can't hurt him!
[gasps loudly]

157
00:08:41,916 --> 00:08:44,166
[growls, gulps]

158
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:47,125
Oh. That's it! You are
paying for that in blood,

159
00:08:47,208 --> 00:08:48,958
-you flea-ridden little bastard!
-[KAZUKI] No!

160
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:54,250
This is making me so anxious.
Why is this happening?

161
00:08:56,208 --> 00:08:57,750
[yells]

162
00:08:58,875 --> 00:09:00,750
Keppi? Let me go!

163
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,250
[groans]
I'm thirsty. I'm so thirsty.

164
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:08,958
[meows]

165
00:09:09,041 --> 00:09:12,000
[panting]
There! I'll skin you alive!

166
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:13,708
-[TOI groaning]
-Nyantaro, run away!

167
00:09:13,791 --> 00:09:14,791
[NYANTARO growls]

168
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:16,291
-Cut it out!
-No, you!

169
00:09:16,375 --> 00:09:18,250
-Just go home!
-No, you!

170
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:20,041
[TOI]
It went in there!

171
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:24,750
[FEMALE SINGER]
Couples.

172
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:28,833
[CROWD cheering]

173
00:09:28,916 --> 00:09:32,833
-[TOI] Let's do this tomorrow.
-[KAZUKI] Good idea.

174
00:09:32,916 --> 00:09:34,833
[NINJA 1]
Hi-yah! Hi-yah!

175
00:09:34,916 --> 00:09:37,958
[NINJA 1] I spy...
two lovey-dovey ninjas!

176
00:09:38,041 --> 00:09:39,833
Now enjoy your date!

177
00:09:39,916 --> 00:09:41,875
[TOI, KAZUKI]
No way!

178
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:43,833
KEPPI:
Positively refreshing!

179
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,833
My dish overfloweth!

180
00:09:45,916 --> 00:09:48,791
-Yeah, yeah, good for you, pal.
-[KEPPI gulping]

181
00:09:48,875 --> 00:09:52,041
[sighs] Kazuki still isn't
replying to my text messages.

182
00:09:52,125 --> 00:09:53,875
-I wonder why?
-[loud slapping]

183
00:09:53,958 --> 00:09:55,958
[mutters]

184
00:09:56,041 --> 00:09:58,500
It's good that you came,
for agents of evil

185
00:09:58,583 --> 00:10:01,083
are encroaching
upon our city as we speak!

186
00:10:01,166 --> 00:10:03,250
-Say what now?
-[cell phone beeps]

187
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:06,166
Uh... it's him!

188
00:10:06,250 --> 00:10:07,875
Oh, wait, no.

189
00:10:07,958 --> 00:10:10,375
Yeah, send me pictures
of your date, sis.

190
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:12,375
That's what I need.

191
00:10:12,458 --> 00:10:15,333
It seems they've forgotten
their noble duty already.

192
00:10:15,416 --> 00:10:17,916
Look at those two.
Without a care in the world!

193
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,666
Huh? What do you mean?
[yells]

194
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:23,666
Kuji and Kazuki?

195
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:25,458
[running footsteps]

196
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:28,916
[TOI]
Hey, cat! I'll kill you!

197
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,541
-[whistle blowing]
-[NINJA 2] Stop right there,

198
00:10:30,625 --> 00:10:31,875
little honey bees!

199
00:10:31,958 --> 00:10:34,208
You aren't following
ninja-couple protocol!

200
00:10:34,291 --> 00:10:36,166
-I want to see the love!
-[running footsteps]

201
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:37,708
[grunts, yells]

202
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:40,208
Sorry, but love is on the plate
today, darling!

203
00:10:40,291 --> 00:10:42,291
-Are you crazy?
-If we don't hold hands,

204
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:44,791
they're gonna kick us
out of the park, you dummy!

205
00:10:44,875 --> 00:10:46,625
[TOI grunting]

206
00:10:46,708 --> 00:10:49,041
-Run! Run for your life!
-Stop running!

207
00:10:50,458 --> 00:10:52,458
[CROWD clamoring]

208
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:57,125
[frustrated chattering]

209
00:10:57,208 --> 00:10:58,916
[TOI]
All the way up there?

210
00:11:00,375 --> 00:11:02,083
[KAZUKI]
Hurry, Nyantaro, he's coming!

211
00:11:02,166 --> 00:11:04,083
[TOI]
Why do you like that crappy cat?

212
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:07,750
I told you! Haruka loves him,
so I have to keep him safe!

213
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:09,875
Okay, who the hell is Haruka?

214
00:11:09,958 --> 00:11:11,416
My brother!

215
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:13,125
He means everything to me.

216
00:11:15,416 --> 00:11:18,166
-I guess I could spare its life.
-[KAZUKI] Really?

217
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:20,583
The next dish
is all mine, though.

218
00:11:20,666 --> 00:11:23,458
The dish? No way.

219
00:11:23,541 --> 00:11:25,583
Well, you can't have it all!
So make a choice!

220
00:11:25,666 --> 00:11:27,166
Don't act like I'm
the unreasonable one,

221
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:28,708
you cat killer!

222
00:11:28,791 --> 00:11:30,208
[OFFICER] We've determined
the identity of the corpse

223
00:11:30,291 --> 00:11:32,458
that was discovered
in the river this morning.

224
00:11:32,541 --> 00:11:35,833
Mokichi Nekoyama.
Thirty-eight. Unemployed.

225
00:11:35,916 --> 00:11:38,166
He was arrested half a year ago
on suspicion

226
00:11:38,250 --> 00:11:40,625
of causing the Asakusa Cat
Shaving Incident,

227
00:11:40,708 --> 00:11:43,250
where cats were abducted
and stripped of their fur.

228
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:45,583
He was eventually released
for lack of evidence,

229
00:11:45,666 --> 00:11:47,666
but no one was ever charged
with the crime.

230
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:50,125
At any rate, we'll be treating
his death as a murder.

231
00:11:52,166 --> 00:11:54,333
And that would be our work,
of course.

232
00:11:54,416 --> 00:11:56,833
Why, it's already
yesterday's news.

233
00:11:56,916 --> 00:12:00,291
[NEKOYAMA] Let meowt!
I'm innocent, I tell mew!

234
00:12:01,541 --> 00:12:03,791
[MABU] For those lost souls
with no beginning,

235
00:12:03,875 --> 00:12:05,916
no end and no connections,

236
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,791
we shall open a brand
new door for you.

237
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,708
[REO]
Is it desire?

238
00:12:13,791 --> 00:12:16,000
Or is it love?

239
00:12:16,083 --> 00:12:18,583
[REO, MABU]
Desire...

240
00:12:18,666 --> 00:12:20,750
-extraction!
-[exploding]

241
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:22,208
[clattering]

242
00:12:22,291 --> 00:12:23,833
[shimmering]

243
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:28,708
[BOTH]
